    Homocysteine, folate, and nonalcoholic fatty liver disease: a systematic review with meta-analysis and Mendelian randomization investigation.
This study suggests a potential role of circulating homocysteine and possibly folate in NAFLD, which calls for future clinical exploration of the possibility of lowering homocysteine levels to prevent NAFLD. Systematic review registration  registered at as CRD42021296434.
